text: Highway 80 is a short East-West Highway in southern Jordan, built in the 1960s.Peter Beaumont, Gerald Blake, J. Malcolm Wagstaff, The Middle East: A Geographical Study, Second Edition, Routledge, (2016), p. 425. It starts from Highway 15 and connects it to Aqaba, 13 km on the west where it ends on Highway 65. ==See also== *Itinerary of the highway on Google maps * ==References== Category:Roads in Jordan
title: Highway 80 (Jordan)
